('2401', '0', '_transient_dash_91cf481bdcff97d36bc4763744848eba', '<h4>\r\n	<a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/W3TOTALCACHE/~3/gFMxnJ8fqs0/cache-plugin-for-multisite-how-to-not-cache-all-sites-in-network\">clvr on &quot;cache plugin for multisite: how to not cache all sites in network?&quot;</a>\r\n</h4>\r\n<p>\r\n	<p>NO WAY! You\'re awesome D! I seriously didn\'t intend / expect for you to jump on it that fast. I thought about taking a crack at it myself, but had no idea when I\'d ever get around to it; and I figured that if you\'re anything similar to as busy as I am (which I\'m sure you are) it wouldn\'t be fair to blatantly ask.  :)</p>\n<p>This will make it practical for us to use Supercache again, so 1 million thank yous. I will take a look and let you know how it goes.\n</p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/W3TOTALCACHE/~4/gFMxnJ8fqs0\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" /></p>\r\n<h4>\r\n	<a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/W3TOTALCACHE/~3/lovUpU5KYmk/caching-plugins-slow-for-wordpress-33\">andy.mcdonald on &quot;Caching plugins slow for Wordpress 3.3&quot;</a>\r\n</h4>\r\n<p>\r\n	<p>Has anyone else experienced that their cache plugins actually slow their site down more than deactivating them all together? I recently upgraded to Wordpress 3.3 and the plugin I\'m using is W3 Total Cache. I noticed that it took a considerable amount of time to navigate through my pages and admin panel. Then I deactivated the plugin and things sped up more than 2x. Whether it\'s just because 3.3 is so new, or it was just cause my own configurations, I just wanted to see if other people noticed this as well. </p>\n<p>Also this is my first time posting on the forums so I\'m seeing what kind of response this might get.\n</p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/W3TOTALCACHE/~4/lovUpU5KYmk\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" /></p>\r\n<h4>\r\n	<a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/W3TOTALCACHE/~3/NujkYWbHD1A/plugin-w3-total-cache-inline-css-minify-problem\">maxidirienzo on &quot;Inline CSS minify problem&quot;</a>\r\n</h4>\r\n<p>\r\n	<p>We are using at out site the latest version of W3 Total Cache on a wordpress 3.3, when I activate the CSS minify option, this inline CSS style:</p>\n<p>&#60;style type=\"text/css\"&#62;.NetCTQ {display:none; visibility:hidden}&#60;/style&#62;</p>\n<p>is converted to:<br />\n&#60;style type=\"text/css\"&#62;&#60;/style&#62;</p>\n<p>These are the minify settings:</p>\n<p>\'minify.css.enable\' =&#62; true,<br />\n\'minify.css.engine\' =&#62; \'csstidy\',<br />\n\'minify.css.combine\' =&#62; false,<br />\n\'minify.css.strip.comments\' =&#62; false,<br />\n\'minify.css.strip.crlf\' =&#62; false,<br />\n\'minify.css.imports\' =&#62; \'process\',<br />\n\'minify.css.groups\' =&#62; array(<br />\n),</p>\n<p>When I turn off the minify setting, the inline style is shown fine.</p>\n<p>can someone give me a hint of what\'s going on?</p>\n<p><a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/w3-total-cache/\">http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/w3-total-cache/</a>\n</p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/W3TOTALCACHE/~4/NujkYWbHD1A\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\n	<a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/W3TOTALCACHE\" target=\"_blank\">View Feed</a>\r\n</p>\r\n', 'no'),
