1:\"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/?p=10864\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~3/mrWfj7803TA/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1222:\"<p><a href=\"http://www.woothemes.com/2011/12/wordpress-in-2012/\">The results are in</a> from the <a href=\"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2011/11/28/woothemes-wordpress-wishlist-survey/\">WooThemes survey</a>. Presented in a handy infographic, this year&#8217;s survey brought to life some interesting facts from the 2,000+ <a href=\"http://wordpress.org/\">WordPress</a> users who took it.</p>\n<p>Among those surveyed, 90% feel that WordPress has graduated from blog publishing tool to full-fledged CMS, 68% use WordPress for sites requiring extensive CMS functionality, 77% make money from WordPress while 31% make their living from it, and 76% find <a href=\"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2011/10/23/wordpress-and-responsive-web-design/\">responsive web design</a> to be an important factor in their theme choice.</p>\n<p>While we&#8217;re on the subject of surveys, you may want to take <a href=\"http://wordpressdotorg.polldaddy.com/s/wordpress-org-site-survey\">this short 5-question survey</a> to help improve the quality of <a href=\"http://wordpress.org/\">the main WordPress.org site</a>.</p>\n<img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~4/mrWfj7803TA\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" />\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Sat, 24 Dec 2011 13:00:49 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http:/